<p><strong>The Purpose of Pentecost: A Q&amp;A with T.L. Osborn</strong></p>
<p><strong>Question: What is the central purpose of the Pentecostal experience?</strong></p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> According to T.L. Osborn, the primary purpose of Pentecost is to empower believers with the Holy Spirit. The Spirit serves as a guide, teacher, comforter, and source of supernatural power for Christians, enabling them to live a victorious and fruitful life.</p>
<p><strong>Question: How does the Holy Spirit enable Christians to live victoriously?</strong></p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> The Holy Spirit provides believers with spiritual gifts and abilities, such as speaking in tongues, healing, and prophecy. These gifts empower them to serve others, intercede for the sick, and spread the gospel of Jesus Christ. Additionally, the Spirit guides Christians in making wise decisions and resisting temptation.</p>
<p><strong>Question: What is the role of the Holy Spirit in the Great Commission?</strong></p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> The Holy Spirit is essential for fulfilling the Great Commission. Believers filled with the Spirit are bold witnesses for Christ, capable of sharing the gospel effectively and leading others to salvation. The Spirit provides power for evangelism, giving believers the courage to proclaim the truth and overcome opposition.</p>
<p><strong>Question: How can Christians receive the Holy Spirit today?</strong></p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Christians can receive the Holy Spirit by faith through prayer and asking Jesus to baptize them. Osborn emphasizes that baptism in the Holy Spirit is a distinct experience from salvation and is available to all believers. It is a necessary step for living a dynamic and Spirit-filled life.</p>
<p><strong>Question: What are some practical benefits of being filled with the Holy Spirit?</strong></p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Believers filled with the Spirit experience joy, peace, and assurance of salvation. They have greater intimacy with God and are able to walk in the fullness of their spiritual inheritance. The Spirit also empowers them to overcome addictions, break generational curses, and witness supernatural manifestations of God's power.</p>